text: The philosopher Toby Ord places the risk of our extinction during the twenty-first century at one in six. Should we manage to avoid a tumble off the precipice, he thinks, it will be our era’s defining achievement. https://t.co/9uUTiFZrOx

text: To escape the bubonic plague, Isaac Newton left London for the near total solitude of his family farm, where he invented calculus, created the science of motion, unravelled gravity, and more. Or so the story goes. https://t.co/y3eBDm2oNH

text: The legal team behind the Trump campaign’s attempts to challenge the election results includes a man nicknamed Thor, a lawyer who called the President a “criminal dirtbag” in 2016, and a raving Rudy Giuliani. https://t.co/i0giVU4Et3
